name: Iron Deficiency? Not Here!
title: Lowest Anemia Rates Among Women
description: In 2019, Guatemala boasted one of the lowest anemia rates among women of reproductive age, with only 7.4% affected. This figure is even lower among non-pregnant women, at just 7%.

name: Young Hands in Factories
title: High Child Employment in Manufacturing
description: In 2015, 22.94% of economically active female children aged 7-14 in Guatemala were employed in the manufacturing sector, highlighting a significant reliance on child labor.
